<?xml version="1.1" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<databaseChangeLog
    xmlns="http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog
                        http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog/dbchangelog-3.6.xsd">

    <!--
        Phase E.5 #3 follow-up (2026-06-02): dedupe dn_item_data_map.

        Context. PR #51 (Phase E.4) shipped the demo seed at
        lc-muw-2026-06-01-seed-demo-data.xml + an explicit fixup at
        lc-muw-2026-06-01-seed-demo-data-fixup.xml. The original M2
        seed inlined 8 dn_item_data_map rows AND the M2 fixup
        registered the same 8 inserts (intent: "if the seed somehow
        skips them, the fixup catches it"). The fixup XML had a XSD
        ordering bug (preConditions after comment) that prevented it
        from parsing on fresh deploys — Phase E.5 A3 (commit
        `1aa4ae7fa`) fixed the order. Net effect on a clean DB after
        A3 lands: 16 rows in dn_item_data_map (8 + 8 duplicates).

        This changeset deletes the duplicates, keeping the row with
        the lowest id per (item_data_id, discrepancy_note_id, study_subject_id)
        tuple. Idempotent: runs once via Liquibase's databasechangelog
        guard; further runs are no-ops via the preCondition below.

        Why a GROUP BY MIN(id) rather than a fancier "keep the row
        that matches the seed convention": the duplicate pairs are
        byte-identical except for the autoincrement id. The seed's
        inline rows arrive first (smaller ids), the fixup re-inserts
        with larger ids. Keeping MIN(id) keeps the seed's row,
        consistent with "the seed is the source of truth".
    -->

    <changeSet author="muw-ophthalmology" id="2026-06-02-prune-dn-item-data-map-duplicates" dbms="postgresql">
        <preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN">
            <!-- Only run if duplicates exist; safe no-op when the DB has
                 already converged or when the seed never ran (test DBs). -->
            <sqlCheck expectedResult="0">
                SELECT CASE WHEN COUNT(*) = COUNT(DISTINCT (item_data_id, discrepancy_note_id, study_subject_id))
                            THEN 0 ELSE 1 END
                FROM dn_item_data_map
                WHERE discrepancy_note_id BETWEEN 1 AND 8
            </sqlCheck>
        </preConditions>
        <comment>Drop duplicate dn_item_data_map rows for the 8 seeded discrepancy notes; keep MIN(id) per tuple</comment>

        <sql splitStatements="false"><![CDATA[
            DELETE FROM dn_item_data_map
            WHERE id IN (
                SELECT id
                FROM (
                    SELECT id,
                           ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
                               PARTITION BY item_data_id, discrepancy_note_id, study_subject_id
                               ORDER BY id
                           ) AS rn
                    FROM dn_item_data_map
                ) ranked
                WHERE ranked.rn > 1
            )
        ]]></sql>
    </changeSet>

</databaseChangeLog>
